text: Jessica Niles (born 14 July 1993) is a Canadian volleyball player. She is part of the Canadian women's national volleyball team. She competed at the 2015 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2016 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2018 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, and 2019 FIVB Volleyball Women's Challenger Cup. She played for the University of Alberta's women's volleyball team and ATSC Kelag Wildcats. == References == Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian volleyball players
